'''Alfa''' is a title given to distinguished figures in [[Guinea]], particularly in the [[Kankan Region]]. It has become known in Guinea as a title of respect, especially amongst the [[Maninka]] and [[Fulbé]] and is commonly given to scholars and learned and religious military leaders.<ref>{{cite book|author1=O'Toole, Thomas |author2=Baker, Janice E. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kIiHwg3Y5u4C&pg=PA3&dq=Historical+dictionary+of+Guinea+Guinean+Press+Agency#v=onepage&q=Alfa&f=false|title=Historical Dictionary of Guinea|publisher=Volume 94 of African historical dictionaries, [[Scarecrow Press]]|year=2005|page=6|isbn=0-8108-4634-9}}</ref>

