The '''Great Mosque of Niono''' is an architecturally significant [[mosque]] located in the city of [[Niono]], in the [[Ségou Region]] of southern [[Mali]].<ref name=unesco>[http://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/5440/ La grande mosquée de vendredi de Niono - UNESCO World Heritage Centre] Retrieved on 2009-03-27.</ref>
==Site description== The mosque was first constructed in 1948 by a team of bricklayers native to [[Djenne]], and it today occupies 1,800 square meters.<ref name=unesco/> It is perhaps the most internationally recognized site in the town of [[Niono]], having received the [[Aga Khan Award for Architecture]] in 1983.<ref>http://archnet.org/library/sites/one-site.jsp?site_id=322</ref>
==World Heritage Status== This site was added to the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage]] Tentative List on March 19, 2008 in the Cultural category.<ref name=unesco/>
